"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The np.insert function is being used incorrectly in this context. The insert operation is modifying the shape of the array along the specified axis, which can lead to a mismatch in dimensions when trying to assign the result back to arr[i]. The original arr[i] has a shape of (4,) and the result of np.insert will have a shape of (5,), causing a ValueError.\", \"patch\": \"6c6\\n< arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)\\n---\\n> arr = np.insert(arr, 1, 3, axis=1)\"}"